column5: How was the  fishing there in 2012?
You're going to be hard pressed for people to give out info on small lakes like that.
Well what other kind of questions do ask on these forums "Fishing God"?
Not those ones when you've got 9 posts and are here for one reason only.  Good luck, go for a drive, fish it and tell us how you made out.

What else do you post?  How about a little intro.  Help answer others questions.  Give a little support to some friends.  Ask totally none fishing related questions.  Talk about hockey.  Stopping smoking.  Losing weight.  Having babies.  Lots of other things to post about.  I didn't fish Cameron in 2012..  So I can't answer your question.
Going to have a hard time making friends here with comments like that.  Stay safe.
Which comments are those? Anyways you stay safe too.!

Fishing is great, take your truck out the ice is 4 feet. What really worked for me there is drilling a complete circle of holes around me and chisling out the useless pieces in between. Then jumping up and down as the vibrations are great attractant.  Good luck out there!
I didn't even know there were fish in that lake. Whenever I stay at Cyprus for camping I always leave the fishing gear at home. Didn't know that anything lived in either of those lakes.
